# API Design Standards

## RESTful API Design Principles

### 1. Resource Naming Conventions
- Use **plural nouns** for resource names
- Use **lowercase** with **hyphens** for multi-word resources
- Be **consistent** across all endpoints

```
✅ Good:
GET /api/customers
GET /api/earning-rules
GET /api/loyalty-points

❌ Bad:
GET /api/customer
GET /api/earningRules
GET /api/loyaltypoint
```

### 2. HTTP Methods Usage
```
GET    - Retrieve resource(s) (safe, idempotent)
POST   - Create new resource
PUT    - Update entire resource (idempotent)
PATCH  - Partial resource update
DELETE - Remove resource (idempotent)
```

### 3. URL Structure Standards
```
Base Pattern: /api/{version}/{resource}/{id}/{sub-resource}

Examples:
GET    /api/v1/customers                    # List customers
GET    /api/v1/customers/{id}               # Get customer
POST   /api/v1/customers                    # Create customer
PUT    /api/v1/customers/{id}               # Update customer
DELETE /api/v1/customers/{id}               # Delete customer
GET    /api/v1/customers/{id}/accounts      # Get customer accounts
POST   /api/v1/customers/{id}/accounts      # Create account for customer
```

## API Response Standards

### 1. Success Response Format
```json
{
  "success": true,
  "data": {
    // Resource data here
  },
  "meta": {
    "timestamp": "2024-01-15T10:30:00Z",
    "version": "v1",
    "requestId": "uuid"
  }
}
```

### 2. Error Response Format
```json
{
  "success": false,
  "error": {
    "code": "VALIDATION_ERROR",
    "message": "Validation failed for the request",
    "details": [
      {
        "field": "email",
        "message": "Email format is invalid"
      }
    ]
  },
  "meta": {
    "timestamp": "2024-01-15T10:30:00Z",
    "version": "v1",
    "requestId": "uuid"
  }
}
```

### 3. Pagination Response Format
```json
{
  "success": true,
  "data": [
    // Array of resources
  ],
  "meta": {
    "pagination": {
      "currentPage": 1,
      "totalPages": 10,
      "totalItems": 100,
      "itemsPerPage": 10,
      "hasNext": true,
      "hasPrevious": false
    },
    "timestamp": "2024-01-15T10:30:00Z",
    "requestId": "uuid"
  }
}
```

## HTTP Status Codes

### Success Codes
- **200 OK**: Successful GET, PUT, PATCH
- **201 Created**: Successful POST
- **204 No Content**: Successful DELETE

### Client Error Codes
- **400 Bad Request**: Invalid request format
- **401 Unauthorized**: Authentication required
- **403 Forbidden**: Access denied
- **404 Not Found**: Resource not found
- **409 Conflict**: Resource conflict
- **422 Unprocessable Entity**: Validation errors

### Server Error Codes
- **500 Internal Server Error**: Unexpected server error
- **502 Bad Gateway**: Upstream service error
- **503 Service Unavailable**: Service temporarily down

## API Versioning Strategy

### 1. URL Path Versioning (Recommended)
```
/api/v1/customers
/api/v2/customers
```

### 2. Version Header (Alternative)
```
GET /api/customers
API-Version: v1
```

### 3. Version Support Rules
- Support **minimum 2 versions** simultaneously
- **Deprecation notice** 6 months before removal
- **Backward compatibility** within major version
- **Clear migration guide** for breaking changes

## Authentication & Authorization

### 1. JWT Token Format
```json
Header:
Authorization: Bearer <jwt-token>

JWT Payload:
{
  "sub": "user-id",
  "iat": 1642251600,
  "exp": 1642338000,
  "roles": ["CUSTOMER", "ADMIN"],
  "customerId": "customer-id",
  "permissions": ["READ_PROFILE", "WRITE_PROFILE"]
}
```

### 2. Role-Based Access Control
```yaml
Roles:
  ADMIN:
    - Full system access
    - User management
    - System configuration
  
  MANAGER:
    - Customer management
    - Campaign management
    - Reports access
  
  CUSTOMER:
    - Own profile access
    - Points management
    - Reward redemption
  
  POS_OPERATOR:
    - Transaction processing
    - Customer lookup
    - Points redemption
```

## Request/Response Specifications

### 1. Common Headers
```
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json
Authorization: Bearer <token>
X-Request-ID: <uuid>
X-Correlation-ID: <uuid>
X-API-Version: v1
```

### 2. Date/Time Format
- Use **ISO 8601** format: `2024-01-15T10:30:00Z`
- Always use **UTC timezone**
- Include timezone offset when local time needed

### 3. Decimal Number Format
- Use **string representation** for monetary values
- Include **currency code** for financial data
```json
{
  "balance": "123.45",
  "currency": "USD"
}
```

## Query Parameters

### 1. Filtering
```
GET /api/customers?status=active&level=gold
GET /api/transactions?dateFrom=2024-01-01&dateTo=2024-01-31
```

### 2. Sorting
```
GET /api/customers?sort=firstName:asc,lastName:desc
GET /api/transactions?sort=date:desc
```

### 3. Pagination
```
GET /api/customers?page=1&limit=20
GET /api/customers?offset=0&limit=20
```

### 4. Field Selection
```
GET /api/customers?fields=id,firstName,lastName,email
```

## Specific API Endpoints

### Customer APIs
```yaml
GET /api/v1/customers:
  description: List customers with filtering and pagination
  parameters:
    - status: [active, inactive, suspended]
    - level: [bronze, silver, gold, platinum]
    - segment: [vip, regular, new]
    - page: integer
    - limit: integer
    - sort: string

GET /api/v1/customers/{id}:
  description: Get customer details
  response: CustomerDetailsDTO

PUT /api/v1/customers/{id}:
  description: Update customer profile
  request: UpdateCustomerRequest
  response: CustomerDetailsDTO

GET /api/v1/customers/{id}/points:
  description: Get customer points balance
  response: PointsBalanceDTO

POST /api/v1/customers/{id}/points/earn:
  description: Add points to customer account
  request: EarnPointsRequest
  response: PointsTransactionDTO
```

### Campaign APIs
```yaml
GET /api/v1/campaigns:
  description: List available campaigns
  parameters:
    - customerId: string (for personalized results)
    - status: [active, inactive, coming_soon]
    - type: [discount, gift, event, delivery]

GET /api/v1/campaigns/{id}:
  description: Get campaign details
  response: CampaignDetailsDTO

POST /api/v1/campaigns/{id}/redeem:
  description: Redeem campaign reward
  request: RedeemRewardRequest
  response: CouponDTO

GET /api/v1/customers/{customerId}/campaigns/purchased:
  description: Get customer's purchased rewards
  response: PurchasedRewardsDTO[]
```

### Transaction APIs
```yaml
POST /api/v1/transactions:
  description: Process new transaction
  request: ProcessTransactionRequest
  response: TransactionDTO

GET /api/v1/transactions/{id}:
  description: Get transaction details
  response: TransactionDetailsDTO

GET /api/v1/customers/{customerId}/transactions:
  description: Get customer transaction history
  parameters:
    - dateFrom: date
    - dateTo: date
    - type: [purchase, points_earn, points_spend]
    - page: integer
    - limit: integer
```

## Data Transfer Objects (DTOs)

### 1. Customer DTOs
```java
public class CustomerDetailsDTO {
    private String customerId;
    private String email;
    private String firstName;
    private String lastName;
    private String phone;
    private LocalDate dateOfBirth;
    private String status;
    private String level;
    private LocalDateTime registrationDate;
    private LocalDateTime lastLoginDate;
    private AddressDTO address;
    private PreferencesDTO preferences;
}

public class UpdateCustomerRequest {
    @NotBlank
    private String firstName;
    
    @NotBlank
    private String lastName;
    
    @Email
    private String email;
    
    @Pattern(regexp = "^\\+?[1-9]\\d{1,14}$")
    private String phone;
    
    private LocalDate dateOfBirth;
    private AddressDTO address;
    private PreferencesDTO preferences;
}
```

### 2. Points DTOs
```java
public class PointsBalanceDTO {
    private String customerId;
    private BigDecimal activePoints;
    private BigDecimal expiredPoints;
    private BigDecimal totalEarned;
    private BigDecimal totalSpent;
    private LocalDateTime lastUpdated;
    private List<PointsExpirationDTO> expirations;
}

public class EarnPointsRequest {
    @NotNull
    @DecimalMin("0.01")
    private BigDecimal points;
    
    @NotBlank
    private String reason;
    
    private String transactionId;
    private Map<String, Object> metadata;
}
```

## API Documentation

### 1. OpenAPI Specification
- Use **OpenAPI 3.0** specification
- Include detailed **descriptions** and **examples**
- Document **all parameters** and **response codes**
- Provide **schema definitions** for all DTOs

### 2. Swagger UI Integration
- Auto-generated from OpenAPI specs
- Include **"Try it out"** functionality
- Provide **authentication** for testing
- Include **example requests/responses**

### 3. API Testing
- **Postman collections** for manual testing
- **Automated API tests** in CI/CD pipeline
- **Contract testing** between services
- **Performance testing** for critical endpoints

## Rate Limiting

### 1. Rate Limit Headers
```
X-RateLimit-Limit: 1000
X-RateLimit-Remaining: 999
X-RateLimit-Reset: 1642251600
```

### 2. Rate Limit Rules
```yaml
Public Endpoints: 100 requests/minute
Authenticated Users: 1000 requests/minute
Admin Users: 5000 requests/minute
System Integration: 10000 requests/minute
```

### 3. Rate Limit Response
```json
{
  "success": false,
  "error": {
    "code": "RATE_LIMIT_EXCEEDED",
    "message": "Too many requests. Try again later."
  },
  "meta": {
    "retryAfter": 60
  }
}
```
